<TEXT>
<P>
 With Jimmy King and Ray Jackson back in the Michigan lineup from one-game 
suspensions and Chris Webber rooting from the end of the bench, 11th-ranked 
Michigan defeated 12th-ranked Indiana, 91-67, on Tuesday night at Ann Arbor, 
Mich., to take over sole possession of first place in the Big Ten Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 King scored 17 points and Jackson 13 for the Wolverines, who never trailed 
while improving to 16-4 overall and 8-2 in the Big Ten. 
</P>
<P>
 Jalen Rose scored 20 points for Michigan and Juwan Howard scored 19. 
</P>
<P>
 Alan Henderson scored 18 points for Indiana (14-5, 7-3) and Damon Bailey 
scored 17. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 2 Duke 66, Georgia Tech 63 -- Marty Clark and Eric Meek came off the bench 
to help the Blue Devils (17-2, 8-2) rally from a 12-point deficit to defeat the 
Yellow Jackets (12-9, 3-7) in an Atlantic Coast Conference game at Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
 The Blue Devils used a 26-6 run over an eight-minute span to take a 46-38 lead 
with 14:42 to play. Meek and Grant Hill each scored eight points and Clark 
seven during the burst. 
</P>
