<P>
IMPRISONING ADDICTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * (President) Clinton's "three strikes you're out" policy will be another 
straw that will help to eventually break the camel's back, which is the prison 
system. The system is already underfunded. 
</P>
<P>
 Is it true that it costs around $40,000 per year to keep a man in prison? 
</P>
<P>
 The solution is to keep them out of prison! 
</P>
<P>
 A huge percentage of violent crime is caused by gangs protecting their sales 
territory for illegl drugs. 
</P>
<P>
 Addicts also have to steal to pay the high prices caused by the black market. 
</P>
<P>
 If we eliminate that black market, the crime will stop. 
</P>
<P>
 This is about freedom. If somebody wants to to kill themselves with drugs, 
they should be free to do it. 
</P>
<P>
 Judge (James) Gray and many others are in agreement on this point. Educated 
people are pro-legalization, not the typical pot-smoking drug addict. 
</P>
<P>
 We need solutions, not dead-end prison terms. 
</P>
<P>
 It was refreshing to see your editorial a while ago. An open mind and a basic 
view of the facts will show the folly of maintaining a hugely profitable black 
market. 
</P>
<P>
 PETER JAMES DAVIDSON 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 
