COLLEGE ROUNDUP; TITANS STAGE BIG RALLY TO BEAT LOYOLA MARYMOUNT IN BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton rallied for 10 runs in the last three innings to defeat 
Loyola Marymount, 15-8, in a nonconference baseball game Tuesday at Loyola. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans (7-1), who won their sixth consecutive game, trailed, 8-5, after 
five innings, but scored three runs in the seventh and eighth innings, and four 
runs in the ninth. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Wagner (1-0), Chad Rolish and Ted Silva combined to shut out Loyola the 
last three innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Designated hitter Adam Millan and second baseman Jeff Ferguson led Fullerton 
offensively. Millan was three for five, scored three runs and drove in two. 
Ferguson had four hits, scored four runs and had four RBIs. They each hit two 
doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 First baseman D.C. Olsen added a double and a solo home run in the ninth. It 
was his first home run of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton starting pitcher Derek Fahs gave up five runs on nine hits in 3 1/3 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola (1-1) scored three runs in the fourth on left fielder Mike Peters' 
three-run inside-the-park homer. Peters had three hits. 
</P>
