<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BellSouth Contemplates Bigger Role in Paramount Bid: Although the final bids 
have been submitted for Paramount Communications Inc., QVC Network Inc.'s 
backers are continuing to explore ways they might prop up the value of QVC's 
offer, a source confirmed.Short-term holders of Paramount stock are favoring 
rival Viacom Inc. because QVC refused to offer any protection against a 
downward spiral in the value of its shares in its cash-and-stock tender offer. 
Traders have been speculating that BellSouth Corp., which has already pledged 
$2 billion in support of the QVC bid, might promise to buy a specific amount of 
QVC shares within several months. "It is being explored," one knowledgeable 
source said. 
</P>
