<P>
PARDON REQUESTS DENIED FOR GREEK JUNTA LEADERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Greek Justice Ministry refused Tuesday to pardon four aging leaders of the 
military junta that ruled the country in the late '60s and early '70s and said 
they must remain in jail. 
</P>
<P>
 A Justice Ministry committee turned down requests by Stylianos Pattakos, 
George Zoitakis, Nikolaos Makarezos and Ioannis Ladas to be pardoned because of 
their failing health. 
</P>
<P>
 The four, serving life sentences, were among the leaders of a 1967 military 
coup and were senior ministers in the dictatorship that ruled Greece until 
1974. 
</P>
