ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; FORUM ON HUMAN AFFAIRS MEETS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Service groups, volunteers and school officials are invited to attend the 
city's Human Affairs Forum today. 
</P>
<P>
 A clearinghouse for community needs, the forum is a monthly event sponsored by 
the city planning department. Any local nonprofit group looking for help with 
its program is encouraged to attend, said city officials. 
</P>
<P>
 The discussion group will meet at the Ole Hanson Beach Club, 105 West Avenida 
Pico, from 3 to 4:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 This month the forum will update San Clemente High School's cultural fair and 
the Interfaith Youth Shelter's winter program. 
</P>
<P>
 For information about the forum, call the city at (714) 498-2533, Ext. 
3316.FRANK MESSINA 
