<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / COSTA MESA / NEWPORT / IRVINE: COSTA MESA; MESA VERDE 
LIBRARY TO GET ROOF REPAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Mesa Verde Library's leaky roof held up under strong rains Monday, and 
could be repaired on Friday when the library is closed, said branch Manager 
Gladys Lorenzo. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council voted unanimously this week to pay for emergency roof 
repairs, estimated to cost between $24,000 and $30,000. 
</P>
<P>
 A leak was discovered two weeks ago when a patron pulled a soggy technical 
book off the reference shelf. Library staff later found that more than a dozen 
books, all out of print, had been destroyed by water, Lorenzo said. 
</P>
<P>
 Workers placed a temporary patch on the roof and covered bookshelves with 
plastic. "It's been holding, but we're not going to take the plastic off," 
Lorenzo said. "I hope it gets done before we get another big leak." 
</P>
<P>
 The library, at 2969 Mesa Verde Drive East, is operated by the county, 
although the city owns and maintains the buildings. Lorenzo said about 500 
people use the library each day, and more than 10,000 books are checked out 
from the library each month. 
</P>
<P>
 The library had to reduce its operation last July from 59 hours weekly to 29 
hours weekly because of county budget cuts. WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
