<P>
FISHING REPORT: CITY FOLKS GET CHANCE TO GET TROUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Department of Fish and Game's "Fishin' in the City" project gets a boost 
this week as rainbow trout will be planted for the first time in five urban 
lakes in Los Angeles County and one in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Trout to a half-pound will be planted at Cerritos Park Lake, Kenneth Hahn Park 
Lake in Baldwin Hills, La Mirada Park Lake, Magic Johnson Park Lake in 
Willowbrook, Lincoln Park Lake in Lincoln Heights, and Mile Square Park Lake in 
Fountain Valley. 
</P>
