<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE BASKETBALL; GOLDEN WEST'S STREAK ON THE LINE TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden West puts its 65-game home winning streak on the line at 7 o'clock 
tonight in an Orange Empire Conference women's basketball game against visiting 
Orange Coast. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rustlers (26-4, 8-1 in conference) are the second-ranked team in Southern 
California.Golden West is coming off a 79-75 overtime loss to Cypress last 
Friday. The loss ended Golden West's 25-game conference winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West leads second-place Fullerton (18-11, 6-2) by 1 1/2 games with 
three left. Riverside (21-9, 4-4) is at Fullerton also at 7 tonight. Fullerton 
has four games remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast (17-10, 5-4) lost to Golden West, 79-71, in overtime in the first 
round. 
</P>
<P>
 In the men's race: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback (19-6, 9-1) holds a one-game lead over Riverside (22-6, 8-2) with 
four left. Saddleback, which won the conference title last season, travels to 
Cypress (12-17, 3-7) for a 7 p.m. game. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside plays host to Fullerton (21-8, 6-4). 
</P>
