<TEXT>
<P>
 Chip Business Increases: The Semiconductor Industry Assn.'s closely watched 
book-to-bill ratio for January jumped to 1.07, up from 1.04 in December.Over 
the last several years, the January ratio has been up from December's. A 
book-to-bill ratio of 1.07 indicates that for every $100 in semiconductor 
shipments to the U.S. market, chip makers received $107 in new orders. A ratio 
above 1 indicates that the market is expanding. Bookings, based on a 
three-month moving average, were $2.456 billion, up 6% from $2.317 billion in 
December. 
</P>
