<P>
 State Home Sales Forecast Revised Upward: Reversing their earlier projections, 
economists at the California Assn. of Realtors said the figure should climb 
2.4% this year but that the price of a typical home should ease 2.5% to 
$184,150.In its initial forecast in September, the group said sales would 
probably drop 2.4% in 1994 and that prices would fall a steeper 3.1%. The 
upward revision was based on stronger-than-expected recent sales trends and an 
improving economy in both California and the rest of the United States, the 
association said. Sales in the state rose 2.2% in 1993 from 1992, it said, but 
the median price of a home fell 4.3% to $188,870. 
