<P>
BRIEFCASE: AUTOMOBILES; DEALERSHIPS IN HUNTINGTON BEACH, COSTA MESA ARE 
SHIFTING THEIR GEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John O'Dell, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The theater and the ballpark aren't the only places you need a program to keep 
the players straight. Recent changes among the car dealerships on Costa Mesa's 
Harbor Boulevard and Huntington Beach's Beach Boulevard ought to keep sign 
makers in champagne for quite a while. 
</P>
<P>
 University Olds-Pontiac-GMC Truck is gone; so is Norm Reeves Acura. Reeves 
went to Huntington Beach and turned into a Honda dealer. 
</P>
<P>
 Roger Miller Honda, on Beach Boulevard, disappeared, but Reeves didn't take 
over that store, which remains empty. Instead, Norm Reeves Honda Superstore 
Huntington Beach -- that's its name -- is housed in what used to be the 
Huntington Beach Acura dealership. 
</P>
<P>
 And Huntington Beach Acura is now on Harbor Boulevard in Costa Mesa, doing 
business as South Coast Acura in the old Reeves Acura facility. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was just one too many Acura dealers around, and this was the best 
solution," said one insider. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, a few blocks to the south on Harbor Boulevard, Orange Coast Jeep 
Eagle has acquired the recently closed University Olds operation, which has 
reopened under the Orange Coast banner. Dealership owner Gary Gray said he 
hasn't picked a new name for the combined operations yet, but is leaning toward 
Orange Coast Auto Center or a variation thereof. 
</P>
</TEXT>
