<P>
 Richard Rapp, Abbey's chief financial officer, would not disclose details of 
the change, saying only that "there will be clarification in the near future." 
</P>
<P>
 Abbey makes home health-care equipment and drugs. Total Pharmaceutical, a 
wholly owned subsidiary, provides drugs and medical equipment for patients 
getting home infusion therapy. 
</P>
<P>
 In Tuesday's Nasdaq trading, Abbey's stock closed at $28.88, up 38 cents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
