<P>
MARINE WHO SHOT SELF AFTER KILLING 2 DIES OF WOUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A young Marine, who kidnaped his estranged wife and killed two people who 
tried to intervene, died Tuesday of wounds from shooting himself. 
</P>
<P>
 Lance Cpl.Timothy Clemons, 22, of Chicago died at 2:45 p.m., said Naval 
Hospital spokeswoman Pat Neal in San Diego. Clemons had been in the hospital 
since shooting himself at noon Monday, when he was confronted by a military 
police officer at his former barracks at Camp Pendleton. 
</P>
<P>
 Clemons kidnaped his estranged wife Sunday night as she left work at a 
Carlsbad mall, police said. He shot to death two of her friends who tried to 
stop the kidnaping, authorities said. The young Marine fled to Mexico with his 
wife, Debra Hearn. 
</P>
