 Hearn managed to persuade her husband to return to the United States on Monday 
morning and free her, officials said. She was unhurt. 
</P>
<P>
 Clemons returned to his old barracks at Camp Pendleton. Someone at the 
barracks called police and when an MP approached with a gun and ordered Clemons 
to surrender, Clemons shot himself, said base Master Sgt. John Farrell. 
