<HEADLINE>
<P>
INFANT GIRL FOUND DEAD IN TRASH; MOTHER IS ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOSH MEYER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities found a dead infant girl in a dumpster Tuesday morning and 
arrested her 17-year-old mother on suspicion of murder. 
</P>
<P>
 The infant was discovered at 8 a.m. when a woman went to take out her trash 
and lifted the lid to the dumpster at 5915 Whitnall Highway in North Hollywood, 
police said.Inside, she found the infant, who was naked and apparently already 
dead, said Lt. Al Moen, officer in charge of the Los Angeles Police 
Department's Child Protection Section. Paramedics were called, and the infant 
was pronounced dead at the scene, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the investigation is continuing, Moen said police determined that a 
teen-ager living next door to the dumpster had concealed her pregnancy from her 
mother, with whom she lived. The girl, who police won't identify because she is 
a juvenile, "admitted giving birth to the infant girl and putting the child in 
the dumpster" shortly afterward, Moen said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Unfortunately, we have too many of these kinds of cases," Moen said. "There 
are plenty of people who would want to adopt children. It's a shame people have 
to resort to this." 
</P>
<P>
 The apparent cause of the infant's death is being withheld pending autopsy 
results, which Moen said should be ready by the end of the week. 
</P>
<P>
 Police today plan to submit a petition to prosecutors in Sylmar Juvenile Court 
asking that the teen-age mother be charged with the equivalent of murder. If 
she is convicted, she could be sentenced to stay in jail until she turns 25, 
Moen said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
